# Keep shell scripts LF even on Windows checkouts.
#
# The `_py.sh` python launcher (and any other *.sh) MUST stay LF: with
# core.autocrlf=true a Windows clone would otherwise get CRLF, and bash then
# fails with `bad interpreter: /usr/bin/env bash^M`. eol=lf overrides autocrlf
# so these files are always checked out with LF.
*.sh text eol=lf
